---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 20, 2026';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Turn a Phrase"
  description="The plain-English terms for using the Turn a Phrase mobile app."
  path="terms"
>
  <div class="container legal">
    <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p>
      These terms govern your use of the Turn a Phrase mobile app and website
      (collectively, the "Service"), operated by <strong>Mocklet Design</strong>.
      By installing or using the Service, you agree to these terms. If you don't,
      please don't use the Service.
    </p>

    <h2>What you can do</h2>
    <p>
      You may install the Service on personal devices you own or control, use it
      for personal, non-commercial language learning, share your individual
      streak / score images on social media, and export your data at any time.
    </p>

    <h2>What you can't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Use the Service to harass, defame, or harm others.</li>
      <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract source code from the app — except where law permits despite this restriction.</li>
      <li>Use automated tools (scrapers, bots, headless clients) to harvest content from the Service.</li>
      <li>Resell, sublicense, or rebrand the Service.</li>
      <li>Impersonate another user or misrepresent your identity.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your account</h2>
    <p>
      You can use the Service as a guest (no account) or sign up with email.
      You're responsible for keeping your sign-in credentials confidential.
      Tell us at <a href="mailto:help@turnaphrase.app">help@turnaphrase.app</a>
      if you suspect unauthorized use.
    </p>
    <p>
      We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms or that
      threaten the safety or integrity of the Service.
    </p>

    <h2>Content</h2>
    <p>
      Idiom dossiers, origins, examples, and other content shown in the Service
      are either drawn from public-domain sources or generated by us with the
      help of language models (Claude, by Anthropic). We provide them
      "as is" for educational use. We do our best to be accurate, but idiom
      etymology is a contested field — if you spot an error, please send it
      to <a href="mailto:help@turnaphrase.app">help@turnaphrase.app</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      The Service's name, brand, design, and code are owned by Mocklet Design
      and protected by copyright and trademark law. You don't acquire any
      ownership rights by using the Service.
    </p>
    <p>
      The content of individual idiom entries (which are largely drawn from public
      sources) is not exclusively ours; you're welcome to use any specific idiom
      definition for your own learning or teaching.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is provided <strong>"as is" and "as available"</strong>, without
      warranties of any kind, express or implied. We don't warrant that the
      Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or that any specific content
      is accurate. The Service is for language learning, not professional
      translation; don't rely on it for legal, medical, or business decisions.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent allowed by law, Mocklet Design is not liable for
      indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising
      from your use of the Service. Our total liability, in any case, will not
      exceed the greater of (a) $20 USD or (b) the amount you paid us in the
      twelve months before the claim arose. (Spoiler: in v1 that amount is $0.)
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to the Service</h2>
    <p>
      We may add, change, or remove features at any time. We may also update
      these terms; the "Last updated" date at the top changes when we do.
      Material changes will be communicated in the app where required by law.
    </p>

    <h2>Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You can stop using the Service at any time. You can delete your account
      from Settings → Account → Delete account. We may terminate or suspend
      accounts that violate these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction where Mocklet
      Design is located, without regard to conflict-of-laws principles. Any
      dispute will be resolved in the courts of that jurisdiction.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Mocklet Design (operator of Turn a Phrase)<br/>
      Email: <a href="mailto:help@turnaphrase.app">help@turnaphrase.app</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
